@startuml
title Optimisation Capability Discovery — ACTIVE Capabilities and Request Contract

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor #EEF2FF
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #4F46E5
skinparam sequenceActorBackgroundColor #EEF2FF
skinparam sequenceActorBorderColor #4F46E5
skinparam noteBorderColor #A5B4FC
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #EEF2FF

actor "User & OEX" as Caller
participant "OGW" as OGW
participant "OSB MS" as OSB
participant "NGW" as NGW
participant "OD MS" as ODMS
database "OD MS DB" as ODDB

== Discovery Request ==

Caller -> OGW : 1. Request available\noptimisation capabilities
OGW -> OGW : 2. Authenticate caller/session\nand derive user context

note right of OGW
User context may include tenant, claims,
roles/scopes, and entitlements.
end note

OGW -> OSB : 3. Invoke OSB MS\nmTLS + User Context JWT\ncorrelationId / traceId

OSB -> OSB : 4. Apply user-context filtering\nand build capability query

note right of OSB
Normal OEX capability browsing defaults to ACTIVE
OptimisationSpecification resources only.

capabilityId maps to OD MS OptimisationSpecification.id
in phase one.

Request guidance exposes expressionSpecification.iri
so runtime expression.iri can be preserved.
end note

OSB -> NGW : 5. Call NGW\nmTLS + OAuth2 system identity\ncorrelationId / traceId\n(no user context downstream)

note right of NGW
User context stops before/at NGW.
Downstream OD MS calls use system/service identity only.
end note

NGW -> ODMS : 6. GET /optimisationSpecification\nlifecycleStatus = ACTIVE\noptional familyId/name/fields filters\nmTLS + service/system auth

note right of ODMS
OD MS authorises the calling service/system.
OD MS does not receive or depend on end-user
identity, claims, roles, or scopes.
end note

== Data Retrieval ==

ODMS -> ODDB : 7. Read visible ACTIVE\nOptimisationSpecification records
ODDB --> ODMS : Specification records\nfamilyId + name + lifecycleStatus\nspecCharacteristic[]\nexpressionSpecification.iri\ntargetEntitySchema metadata

== Discovery Response ==

ODMS --> NGW : 8. Return capability and\nrequest-contract metadata
NGW --> OSB : 9. Return response to OSB MS

OSB -> OSB : 10. Shape CapabilityCard\nor RequestFormModel

note right of OSB
specCharacteristic[] is UI/discovery guidance.
targetEntitySchema remains authoritative.
OSB form validation is pre-validation only.
OC MS remains final runtime contract validator.
end note

OSB --> OGW : 11. OEX-friendly capability view\nwith backend correlation/trace details
OGW --> Caller : 12. Available optimisation capabilities\nand request-contract guidance

@enduml
